      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Kling Image-to-Video Animation (with AI Motion Prompt)\n\nThis flow converts a **final image** into a stylized **video** using PiAPI (Kling), with animated motion prompts generated by OpenAI.\n---\n\n#### üß† **AI Motion Prompt**\n- **OpenAI Node:**\n  - Analyzes the `Final_Image` using `chatgpt-4o-latest`\n  - Generates a motion-aware video prompt\n  - Adds dynamic **camera movement** and **scene action** naturally\n---\n\n#### üß† **Model Routing**\n- **Switch Node:**\n  - Branches based on `\"Choose model for Video\"` field from `TM_GetStatus`\n  - Currently routes to **Kling**, with support for future models like `Veo2`\n---\n\n#### üéûÔ∏è **Video Generation**\n- **Kling Image to Video Node:**\n  - Uses prompt and image to generate video (aspect ratio `9:16`)\n  - Starts the async task and returns `task_id`\n---\n\n#### ‚è≥ **Status Polling**\n- **PiAPI Task Status + Wait + Retry:**\n  - Checks task status in a loop\n  - If still not `completed`, it waits 60 seconds and retries (max 5 tries)\n\n- **IF (Image Ready):**\n  - If status is `completed` ‚Üí proceed\n  - Else ‚Üí re-check status after wait\n\n- **If if failed drop error:**\n  - If status is not `\"failed\"` ‚Üí continue retry loop\n  - If status is `\"failed\"` ‚Üí route to **Stop and Error**\n---\n\n#### ‚ùå **Error Handling**\n- **Stop and Error:**\n  - Terminates the flow if video generation failed\n  - Displays `Failed to generate` error to execution log\n---\n\nüìå **Flow Purpose Summary:**\n- Enables animated video output from static caricature images\n- Adds realistic motion prompts for cinematic video output\n- Ensures task completion before continuing\n",
        "height": 1120,
        "width": 980
      },
